However, Cogeco Câble's revenues increased by 45% to 470.4 million.
The company lost 15,237 customers in the fourth quarter.
However, for the 2013 fiscal year, Cogeco Cable's number of customers is up 5546.
Mr. Audet is not concerned that the number of clients will fluctuate in this way.
For me, this is not an indication of a change in trend, he observed.
It varies from quarter to quarter with very strong competition.
Horse in beef products
Horse meat was detected in cans of beef products sold by two small UK low-priced retailers, the food hygiene agency announced today.
Routine tests revealed that the products, developed in January in Romania and sold by the Home Bargains and Quality Save chains, contained horse DNA at a height of 1 to 5%.
"Since horsemeat is not mentioned in the list of ingredients, it should not have been present in the product," the British agency explained.
A scandal about the presence of horsemeat in cooked dishes broke out in Europe at the beginning of the year, following tests carried out in Ireland.
According to reviews by the European Commission, France was the country most affected by the presence of this type of meat in products intended to contain only beef.
