For Titan's CEO, "Goodyear Amiens' purchase project starts with zero employees"
After throwing the sponge in January for the partial resumption of Amiens-Nord's Goodyear site promised to close, Maurice Taylor, CEO of the American tirematician Titan, today declares himself ready to save 333 jobs out of the 1,137 that the factory counts.
Arnaud Montebourg, Minister for Productive Recovery, had already announced this on Monday, October 21.
