This is what I think: very soon, the unique anti-European and anti-currency sentiment in Europe will unite and eventually kill the euro.
The EU will not disappear, but it will return to something more like the free "Europe of Nations (sovereigns)" favoured by General de Gaulle.
Germany and some of its satellite economies could retain the euro, but France and southern Europe will return to their own currency.
I expect the United Kingdom to distance itself from this project, and I hope it will look soft in the United States.
