But Mr. Hare rejected the idea that the YMCA had a cultural problem preventing staff from reporting Lord's shortcomings in the safety of children.
Staff members testified that they had observed some shortcomings, including the fact that Lord was alone with the children, that he kept them in private, that he had them seated on his lap, that he loved them and let them play with his mobile phone.
Danielle Ockwell, who was under Lord's guidance and had asked for child protection training because she was concerned about her behaviour, said that she found YMCA Caringbah's child services manager, Jacqui Barnat, who supervised Lord "very intimidating and difficult to approach most of the time."
The Director General stated that he rejected the staff's evidence that they were reluctant to report these deficiencies to their supervisor.
